items.title: Broader indices outperform; 48 smallcaps give double digit return
items.description: All the sectoral indices ended in the red with BSE Realty shed 8 percent, BSE Auto index shed 6 percent, BSE Telecom index fell 5 percent, BSE Energy index declined nearly 5 percent.

items.title: Market snaps 3-week run, post biggest weekly drop since 2022
items.description: The Indian rupee ended 27 paise lower against the US dollar in the week ended October 4.

items.title: Chartist Talks: Sudeep Shah of SBI Securities sees potential opportunities for investors in IT sector given strong technical indicators
items.description: Despite consolidation, the Nifty IT has strongly outperformed the frontline indices, said Sudeep Shah of SBI Securities.
